Place the banner near the very top of the DOM, just after the main content skip link.
Wrap the banner in a <div role="region"> with an aria-label saying something like "cookie consent banner" so that people using screen readers know exactly where the banner begins and ends, and can easily skip it with a keyboard shortcut.
<html>
<body>
  <a href="#main" class="skip-to-content">Skip to main content</a>
  <div role="region" aria-label="cookie consent banner" class="cookie-banner">
    <div class="text">This site uses cookies.</div>
    <div class="buttons">
      <button class="accept">Accept</button>
      <button class="dismiss">Dismiss</button>
    </div>
  </div>
  ...
</body>
</html>
